Apparently there has to be content in the rows to hide it.

But i noticed another strange behaviour. When i hide rows like this: 

```
for (let rowNum = 162; rowNum <= 175; rowNum++) {
            const row = worksheet.getRow(rowNum);
            row.hidden = true;
            row.commit();
 }
```
 
 and also outline them like this: 
 
```
 for (let i = 147; i <= 199; i++) {
            worksheet.getRow(i).outlineLevel = 1;
 }

```
The rows are hidden when i export the file, but when i fold rows 147 to 199 and unfold them again. They are no longer hidden...
